comments.text:
The year is 7533. Archeologists have been piecing together the parts required to reboot an ancient storage device. Legend has it that this device used to be able to hold only 1 terabite of data, a tiny amount compared to current times. Upon succeeding, scientists triumphantly dance and celebrate. As they file through each folder, it is revealed to be a backup for the most important data of the "Old Net", a digital time capsule meant to pass on what humans knew in the ancient year of 2021. They find missile launch codes, Political values, and other information now obsolete due to the passage of time.

But there is one last folder.

Their hands shake as they hover over it.
What is this folder?
What is inside that needed to be locked behind 16 locked and compressed folders?





They click it.




It's this video.

comments.text:
Tamers actually is obsessed with sonic underground, and he is a strange and gay person, he likes making videos like this without being satirical. However he is somewhat self aware, and plays a character who is a more obsessed and stupid version of himself. He satirizes himself and his content, in a way, but that is not the only reason he makes videos. He does genuienly enjoy bartelby x sonic shipping, etc.

Also, see how a lot of commentators like to jokingly give him excessive praise or admiration. Of course they are overexagurating, but they actually do like his content. But they praise him in such a way that it could be considered a joke. 
This is very similar to how tamers makes his videos, actually. Both tamers and many of his viewers are ambiguous about things. Either for comedic value, or because deep down, a part of them is insecure and ashamed.
